introduction.p:
The linear threshold model  is a dynamic process for diffusion of innovation on a network. We are given a network and a threshold 0 < q < 1. The network starts with all vertices using behavior B. We pick a seed set of innovators who adopt behavior A.

We then watch the innovation spread according to the following rule.
The vertex v will:





 adopt behavior A if {p \geq q}






 adopt behavior B if {p < q}




We cycle through all the vertices until the update process stabilizes. The resulting adoption process is called a cascade. We have a complete cascade when every vertex adopts the new behavior A.

statement.p:
Now set the threshold q=1/2. Using the same graph as in problem 1,
determine the cascades for each of the following sets S_0 of early adopters. Which initial sets induce complete cascades?






 S_0 = \{1,2\}






 S_0 = \{2,3\}






 S_0 = \{1, 5\}












 S_0 = \{1,2\}:  complete cascade






 S_0 = \{2,3\}:  complete cascade






 S_0 = \{1, 5\}:  only vertex 7 adopts the innovation
